{
  "texts": [
    "Since in our closed-book QA setup the train and test sets are disjoint, the model has to rely on its pre-existing knowledge to answer test questions.",
    "Given a (q, a) pair, P(True) reflects the probability that the model assigns for a being the answer to q.",
    "It can be applied on a model-generated answer for self-evaluation as was done in the original study, or on the ground-truth answer to check whether M considers it as correct, like done in our study.",
    "This is a preliminary analysis, and we leave a comprehensive comparison for future work.",
    "More details in §K."
  ]
}